Many wild mushrooms look safe but can be deadly. Even experts can make mistakes identifying them.

## The Golden Rule
- NEVER eat any wild mushroom you cannot identify with 100% certainty
- "When in doubt, throw it out"
- Cooking does not make poisonous mushrooms safe

## Dangerous Mushrooms
- **Death cap** (Amanita): most deadly, looks like edible mushrooms
- **Destroying angel**: all white, very toxic
- Many others look similar to edible varieties

## Symptoms of Mushroom Poisoning
- Nausea, vomiting, diarrhea
- Stomach pain
- Confusion
- Symptoms can appear hours to days later

## What to Do
- Call Poison Control: 1-800-222-1222
- Try to identify the mushroom (save a sample)
- Go to the emergency room if symptoms are severe
- Tell doctors when the mushroom was eaten`,
