      explanation: `## Toxin-Based Classification

### Amatoxin Syndrome (Amanita phalloides, A. virosa)
- Onset: 6-24 hours
- Phase 1 (6-24h): GI symptoms (may remit)
- Phase 2 (24-48h): apparent recovery
- Phase 3 (48-96h): hepatic failure
- Mortality: 10-30% with treatment

### GI Irritant Syndrome (Multiple species)
- Onset: 30 min - 3 hours
- Nausea, vomiting, diarrhea
- Self-limited (6-24 hours)
- Low mortality

### Muscarinic Syndrome (Inocybe, Clitocybe)
- Onset: 30 min - 2 hours
- SLUDGE: Salivation, Lacrimation, Urination, Defecation, GI distress, Emesis
- Miosis, bradycardia
- Treatment: atropine

### Hallucinogenic (Psilocybe)
- Onset: 30 min - 2 hours
- Hallucinations, euphoria
- Self-limited
- Supportive care

## Amatoxin Management
- Aggressive IV fluids
- Activated charcoal (if early)
- N-acetylcysteine (hepatoprotective)
- Silymarin (milk thistle extract)
- Liver transplant evaluation if severe
- Poison center consultation essential`,
