### Amatoxin Mechanism
- Cyclic octapeptide toxins
- RNA polymerase II inhibition
- Impaired mRNA synthesis
- Hepatocyte death
- Enterohepatic recirculation prolongs exposure

### Gyromitrin Toxicity
- Hydrolyzed to monomethylhydrazine
- Inhibits pyridoxine-dependent enzymes
- GABA synthesis impairment
- Hepatotoxicity
- Hemolysis, seizures

### Orellanine Syndrome
- Cortinarius species
- Delayed onset (2-14 days)
- Tubulointerstitial nephritis
- Often irreversible renal failure

## Amatoxin Management Protocol

### Decontamination
- Activated charcoal if <1-2 hours
- Consider repeat dosing (enterohepatic circulation)

### Specific Therapies
| Agent | Mechanism | Evidence |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| NAC | Hepatoprotection, replenishes glutathione | Recommended |
| Silymarin | Hepatocyte membrane stabilization | Animal data, commonly used |
| Penicillin G | Displaces amatoxin from albumin | Limited evidence |

### Monitoring
- Serial LFTs (AST, ALT, INR)
- Creatinine, electrolytes
- Factor V level (prognostic)
- Mental status

### Transplant Criteria
- INR >6
- Bilirubin >25 after 4 days
- Factor V <10%
- Encephalopathy
- Concurrent renal failure`,
