      explanation: `## Advanced Toxicology

### Amatoxin Molecular Mechanism
- Bicyclic octapeptide structure
- Binds RNAP II bridge helix
- Inhibits translocation
- mRNA synthesis arrest
- Accumulation of protein synthesis defect
- Mitochondrial dysfunction
- Apoptosis pathway activation

### Hepatocyte Death Pathways
- Intrinsic apoptosis (mitochondrial)
- ER stress response
- Secondary necrosis
- Sterile inflammation

### Toxin Kinetics
- Rapid GI absorption
- Hepatic uptake via OATP transporters
- Enterohepatic circulation
- Renal excretion of metabolites

## Evidence-Based Management

### N-Acetylcysteine
- Replenishes glutathione stores
- May interrupt apoptosis cascade
- Standard dosing per acetaminophen protocol
- Limited human data but widely recommended

### Silymarin (Silibinin)
- Inhibits OATP1B3 (reduces hepatic uptake)
- Antioxidant properties
- IV formulation in Europe
- Oral absorption limited

### Hemofiltration/MARS
- Removes circulating toxin
- May interrupt enterohepatic cycle
- Case reports suggest benefit
- Not standard of care

## Prognostic Models

| Parameter | Poor Prognosis |
|-----------|----------------|
| Peak ALT | >3000 IU/L |
| PT/INR | >6 |
| Factor V | <10% |
| Creatinine | Rising |
| Encephalopathy | Present |
| Onset to Rx | >36 hours |

## Special Considerations

### Pediatric Amatoxin
- Higher mortality historically
- Early aggressive intervention
- Lower transplant threshold

### Amatoxin in Pregnancy
- Crosses placenta
- Fetal hepatotoxicity reported
- Aggressive treatment warranted

### Legal Considerations
- Intentional poisoning cases
- Forensic mushroom identification
- Chain of custody for samples`,
